   <concept id="FAR_4_702" class="- topic/topic concept/concept " xtrc="">
      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph class="- topic/ph " props="autonumber">4.702</ph> Applicability.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body concept/conbody ">
         <ol id="d228e13" class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d230e10">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
                  
						            This subpart applies to records generated under contracts that contain one of the following clauses:</p>
               <ol id="d228e23" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d230e16">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        
								                Audit and Records-Sealed Bidding (<xref href="52.214-26.dita#FAR_52_214_26"
                              base="i1060206"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">52.214-26</xref>).</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d230e24">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        
								                Audit and Records-Negotiation (<xref href="52.215-2.dita#FAR_52_215_2"
                              base="i1059150"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">52.215-2</xref>).</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d230e32">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph> This subpart is not mandatory on Department of Energy contracts for which the Comptroller General allows alternative records retention periods. Apart from this exception, this subpart applies to record retention periods under contracts that are subject to <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid%3AUSC-prelim-title10-chapter137&amp;saved=%7CZ3JhbnVsZWlkOlVTQy1wcmVsaW0tdGl0bGU0MC1jaGFwdGVyMzctZnJvbnQ%3D%7C%7C%7C0%7Cfalse%7Cprelim&amp;edition=prelim"
                        scope="external"
                        format="html">10 U.S.C. chapter 137</xref> legacy provisions ( <xref href="https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title10-section3064&amp;num=0&amp;edition=prelim"
                        format="html"
                        scope="external">10 U.S.C. 3064</xref>) and <xref href="https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title10-section3016&amp;num=0&amp;edition=prelim"
                        format="html"
                        scope="external">10 U.S.C. 3016</xref> and chapter 203, or <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title40-section101&amp;num=0&amp;edition=prelim"
                        scope="external"
                        format="html">40 U.S.C. 101</xref>, <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">et seq</i>.</p>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </conbody>
   </concept>
